{"id":"2210.11857","submitter":"Xiaoyu Feng","authors":"Xiaoyu Feng, Zhonghua Qiao, Shuyu Sun, Xiuping Wang","title":"An energy-stable Smoothed Particle Hydrodynamics discretization of the\n  Navier-Stokes-Cahn-Hilliard model for incompressible two-phase flows","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1016/j.jcp.2023.111997","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.flu-dyn","license":"http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/","abstract":"  Varieties of energy-stable numerical methods have been developed for\nincompressible two-phase flows based on the Navier-Stokes-Cahn-Hilliard (NSCH)\nmodel in the Eulerian framework, while few investigations have been made in the\nLagrangian framework. Smoothed particle hydrodynamics (SPH) is a popular\nmesh-free Lagrangian method for solving complex fluid flows. In this paper, we\npresent a pioneering study on the energy-stable SPH discretization of the NSCH\nmodel for incompressible two-phase flows. We prove that this SPH method\ninherits mass and momentum conservation and energy dissipation properties at\nthe fully discrete level. With the projection procedure to decouple the\nmomentum and continuity equations, the numerical scheme meets the\ndivergence-free condition. Some numerical experiments are carried out to show\nthe performance of the proposed energy-stable SPH method for solving the\ntwo-phase NSCH model. The inheritance of mass and momentum conservation and the\nenergy dissipation properties are verified numerically.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Oct 2022 10:24:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-22"}
{"id":"2210.11858","submitter":"Avichai Marmor","authors":"Avichai Marmor","title":"Tight Lower Bound for Pattern Avoidance Schur-Positivity","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  For a set of permutations (patterns) $\\Pi$ in $S_k$, consider the set of all\npermutations in $S_n$ that avoid all patterns in $\\Pi$. An important problem in\ncurrent algebraic combinatorics is to find pattern sets $\\Pi$ such that the\ncorresponding quasi-symmetric function is symmetric for all $n$. Recently,\nBloom and Sagan proved that for any $k \\ge 4$, the size of such $\\Pi$ must be\nat least $3$ unless $\\Pi \\subseteq \\{[1, 2, \\dots, k],\\; [k, \\dots, 1]\\}$, and\nasked for a general lower bound.\n  We prove that the minimal size of such $\\Pi$ is exactly $k - 1$. The proof\napplies a new generalization of a theorem of Bose from extremal combinatorics.\nThis generalization is proved using the multilinear polynomial approach of\nAlon, Babai and Suzuki to the extension by Ray-Chaudhuri and Wilson to Bose's\ntheorem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Oct 2022 10:24:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-10-24"}
